Author: PROSENSE.tv
Title: Prosense live ICO! World's first decentralized VR platform!
Body: We suggest you to take a look at the recent SuperData report: https://vrscout.com/news/global-vr-hardware-revenue-forecaset/   Video content streaming already makes up more than 15% of VR software market and its value is supposed to hit 200 mln dollars by the end of 2017 due to upcoming second generation of VR headsets ( https://www.vrandfun.com/holiday-season-might-define-outcome-vr-industry/ ) .  We suggest that SuperData estimation could be exceeded but even in case it won't, there is still gonna be almost 4 billion dollars in the market (and 600 mln for streaming / video content in particular). UGC (User-generated content) development will be caused by the release of the new video cameras (https://vr.google.com/vr180) supposed to be a more casual analogues of our designs being in use for the last two years.  Taking all this info into consideration, one can be confident, that developing projects like ours is the right thing to do at this particular moment in VR history. If we deviver our platform on time, no doubt-it shall succeed!

Author: PROSENSE.tv
Title: Prosense live ICO! World's first decentralized VR platform!
Body: First and foremost, ICO is a great way to make more people buy the tokens not just for the speculations but also for using them at the platform as it is meant to be. Marketing our ICO will help us to raise the awareness of the existence of our platform among the VR users as well. We believe this will give us a good kickstart as there will be those VR enthusiasts who will buy the tokens to start working with the platform right away. Secondly, we would like our platform to be as much decentralized as it is possible- we believe that people should be free to choose what they want to film, share, broadcast and advertise. Every single large investor who approached us before was trying to offer to implement some sort of control and introduce certain rules on the platform which would help them to accumulate more profit ( e.g- making users show the investors adds, introduce various broadcast costs for different types of content etc). We don’t want Prosense Live to become a second youtube. So, to summarize, we have the tech, we have the concent, we have specialists, we have the experience: we would like to share it not just to sell it. This is why our platform will be different. Whoever will get the tokens will run their own show. By selling tokens we get users and this is most important for us. Hope you got the idea

Author: PROSENSE.tv
Title: Prosense live ICO! World's first decentralized VR platform!
Body: Our platform is peer to peer solution with the blockchain imbedded into it. Maximum security and copyright protectin is our main priority! Here is how it's going to work:  - Video content is encoded with Broadcaster keys and placed in the cloud storage.  - Information about content, metadata and token price and content decryption keys is placed in the blockchain.  - To access the video, the client has to pay the cost of the content, the payment information is stored in the blockchain, the user receives the address for downloading the content, the keys for decryption and viewing, the broadcaster receives the tokens to his address.  - Before the broadcast, a key is created to decode the broadcast and, together with the data on the broadcast, the price of viewing is placed in the blockchain.  - During the broadcast, the video stream from the Broadcast is transferred to our cloud services, transcoded into the formats required for viewing, encoded with a broadcast key and placed on the CDN network.

Some of our differences with other projects:  - we have a global experience in carrying out VR-translations at the highest level. More than 3 years we produce VR-content in partnership with the largest brands  - right now we have signed contracts with various rights holders  - own R & D unit creating advanced solutions for virtual reality  - program modules for transmission and transcoding of signals, hi-end cameras for broadcasts.  Please note, we are trying to offer a decentralized solution based on  the blockchain technology. You choose what content to upload, whom exactly to broadcast it to, who exactly will see that and who will pay. Quicker monetization, better transparency, freedom to chose wheter you want to advertize anything and no middle man inbetween the contentmaker and content consumer. That's the idea

Author: Jdope
Title: Prosense live ICO! World's first decentralized VR platform!
Body: ProsenseLive. World’s first decentralized VR platform  The first global decentralized platform for VR content distribution with intellectual property protection by blockchain technology, guaranteed confidentiality and a built-in payment mechanism.  OFFICIAL WEBSITE: ico.prosense.tv DOWNLOAD THE WHITEPAPER:Whitepaper ONE-PAGER: One-pager  Follow us  Facebook / Youtube / Telegram / Twitter / Instagram / Medium  ICO start date: Nov. 3, 2017, at 10:00 a.m. PDT (6:00 p.m. CET) ICO end date: Dec. 28, 2017, at 9:00 a.m. PST (6:00 p.m. CET)  Pre ICO start date:19 october 2017 Pre ICO end date:31 october 2017  Total token issue: 720,000,000 Token type: ERC20 Ticker:VRP Base price:1 Token = $0,1 Hard Cap:$30M  No tokens will be issued after ICO Undistributed tokens will be eliminated after ICO  Prosense Token VRP is a secure, internal currency that will be used by viewers to pay providers directly for the live content they want to experience. Tokens will only be issued during the ICO, if any remain undistributed after the ICO is completed they will be eliminated.  Please note: there is NO BOUNTY PROGRAM    About Prosense  Prosense is a working business with an already existing highly functional platform for filming, transporting and viewing professional VR broadcasts. We have more than three years of experience in VR content production and technology development. Prosense transforms the technology of centralized content delivery into a global decentralized peer-to-peer platform with a payment collection system in which intellectual property rights are protected by blockchain cryptography and all transactions are confidential.  ProsenseLive Platform  The platform allows any manufacturer of VR-content, whether it is a professional studio or amateur enthusiast, to deliver content to viewers in real time. Encryption, transcoding and delivery of content are carried out by a decentralized network of Prosense Nodes partners who are reimbursed with tokens. Copyright protection and payments to content providers are guaranteed and robustly protected through the use of blockchain technology. The ProsenseView application, adapted for all common types of VR equipment, allows you to participate in breathtaking adventures: gain new experiences while moving around in the broadcast (e.g. watch a goal being scored from the position of the goalie), see and discuss what is happening with your friends, and create your own virtual space and avatars.      The ProsenseLive platform is used for both professional and amateur VR content: online broadcasts of sporting events, concerts, shows, conferences, amateur events or adult content. The quality of the technology used for live VR broadcasts from Prosense gives you the illusion of presence and allows you to participate in breathtaking adventures from the comfort of your home.          Escrow All funds received during the ICO will be stored in a secure Escrow account provided by Blockchain Law Group. The funds will be transferred to Prosense only after all the obligations to the buyers of our tokens are fulfilled.  Team        More about ProsenseLive: ico.prosense.tv More about Prosense: prosense.tv  Media mentions and listings  Forbes Coinspeaker Bitcoinist BlockchainNews Cointelegraph VRFocus Virtual Reality Reporter TheVirtualReport.Biz ICO Alert ICO Ship   Follow us  Facebook / Youtube / Telegram / Twitter / Instagram / Medium   Disclaimer: I'm not the developer or in anyway affiliated with Prosense, i am just the poster of this thread, if you want to contact a representative of Prosense please Pm Prosense.tv.

Scott Ross is an American digital media executive with a career spanning four decades. Most recently he was the Founder, Chairman, and CEO of Digital Domain, Inc., one of the largest digital production studios in the motion picture and advertising industries.  Under Ross' direction, from 1993-2006, Digital Domain garnered two Academy Awards and three nominations, receiving its first Oscar in 1997 for the ground-breaking visual effects in Titanic. In the 80’s Ross was General Manager of Lucasfilm’s Industrial Light and Magic, which, under his direction won 5 Oscars. In 1991 Ross was named VP of the LucasArts Entertainment Group. Ross is a member of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences (OSCARS) and the Academy of Television Arts and Sciences (EMMYS).

Body: Fantastic news: Jesse Damiani, Editor-at-Large for VRScout, CEO & Co-Founder of Galatea, has joined our Advisory Board! Jesse is an entrepreneur, journalist, and public figure in emerging technology. He is Editor-at-Large of VRScout and CEO of Galatea, a writing and project management tool for VR and AR stories. He regularly covers VR, blockchain, and media in Billboard, Quartz, IndieWire, and HuffPost, with syndication in CBS News, The New Digital Storytelling textbook, and REDEF. He was listed as a top global VR influencer in 2017 by Onalytica, was interviewed as an expert source in AP’s guide for immersive journalism, and runs “Blockchain + XR.”
